  "lineCount": 84,
  "lines": [
    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "week, or 400 per month.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "PRESENT RESEARCH WORK",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "(PAGE 4)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "All reports received are checked for source of report; all observers and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "newspapers printing reports are written to request any further details available,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "especially with drawings. An average of 35 newspapers and 35 eyewitnesses are",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "written each month, of the more authentic reports.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "All reports are checked for time, longitude-latitude, in case an object was",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "observed in 2 places within a short time. Reports are also compared against",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "previous reports, for similarity to 2 basic saucer types. These now include:",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "1. Tiny spherical objects, 8 to 12\" diameter.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "2. Small saucers, about 40 feet in diameter.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "3. Large saucers, ranging between 100-250 feet.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "4. Cylindrical objects, about 40' in diam.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "5. Triangular objects, resembling deltaplanes",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "now being tested by many airforces.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "6. Rocket-like objects, between 200 and 300",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "feet long.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "7. Huge cigar-shaped objects,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "possibly between 1,000 and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "2,000 feet long.(See new",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "Keyhoe book)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "8. Huge green fireballs,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "possibly some sort of sig-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "nal devices.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "9. Color changing brilliant",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "lights possible some sort",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "of signal.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "Historical reports are also checked, but are very difficult to locate, and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "very costly to buy. Many appear to be cylindrical objects rather than saucers",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "like, but are equally mysterious in origin. All results of the FLYING SAUCER",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "RESEARCHERS are printed in the group magazine, FLYING SAUCER REVIEW.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "CONCLUSIONS ON SAUCER ORIGIN",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "The result of the many studies made on this subject by almost all civilian",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "groups, and some government groups, is that saucers are unquestionably from space.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "From our own research as the first saucer group, we find that reports of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "the past 7 years definitely tie in with approaches of Mars. Four huge increases",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "of reports occurred on these dates:",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "1. July - Oct; 1946 Hundreds of 'Ghost Rocket' reports over Sweden.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "2. June - July 1947 Hundreds of reports over entire USA.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "3. March - April 1950 Hundreds of reports over entire world.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "4. July - Aug. 1952 Huge increase in reports over USA, and world.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "text": "If the saucers are from another planet, one would expect reports to in-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 56,
      "text": "crease greatly as that planet approaches Earth, and a crossing becomes much",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 57,
      "text": "shorter.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 58,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 59,
      "text": "A check of all planetary position shows Mars was very close on 3 occasions:",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 60,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 61,
      "text": "Jan. 1, 1946 MARS CLOSE OPPOSITION",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 62,
      "text": "MARCH 23, 1950 MARS CLOSE OPPOSITION",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 63,
      "text": "MAY 7, 1952 MARS CLOSE OPPOSITION",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 64,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 65,
      "text": "Our conclusions are that the source of the flying saucers is probably Mars.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 66,
      "text": "Their takeoff occurring just before the close approach of the planet, and arrival",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 67,
      "text": "preceding several months after the approach. Present day rocket scientists state",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 68,
      "text": "their calculations show this is the best method for an approach or interplanetary",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 69,
      "text": "flight, since a flight at any other time would have to cross 2 to 6 times",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 70,
      "text": "the distance. This would represent an increase from the small 35 million mile",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 71,
      "text": "flight to 70 million up to 220 million miles.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 72,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 73,
      "text": "The sole exception appears to be the June - July 1947 reports, but Donald",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 74,
      "text": "Keyhoe stated in his first book that the European 'Ghost Rocket' sightings oc-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 75,
      "text": "curred in small numbers as late as Dec. 1946; whereas the first flying saucers",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 76,
      "text": "were seen in the US in Jan. 1947, and reached their tremendous peak in July 1947",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 77,
      "text": "with hundreds of reports per day.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 78,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 79,
      "text": "This is generally taken to mean the first wave of saucers was actually part",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 80,
      "text": "of the first phase of 'ghost rocket' sightings, and not directly from Mars as in",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 81,
      "text": "following reports. Keyhoe has theorised they are un-manned, remote-controlled recon-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 82,
      "text": "naisance craft, while the thick rocket-like objects were passenger carriers.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 83,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 84,
      "text": "On the basis of these increases, it was predicted in the #2 issue of the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    }
  ],
